column496: Several years of experience may replace formal education and training.
column497: Employers may require applicants to provide a hairstyling demonstration before being hired.
column498: Trade certification for hairstylists is compulsory in Nova Scotia
column504: Red Seal endorsement is also available to qualified hairstylists upon successful completion of the interprovincial Red Seal examination.
column505: Barbers<ul style=\'list-style-type: disc\'><li>Some secondary school education is required.
column506: Completion of a two-year apprenticeship or other barber program is usually required.
column507: On-the-job training may be substituted for formal education.
column508: Trade certification for barbers is available
column509: in British Columbia and the Yukon.
column510: Red Seal endorsement is also available to barbers
column512: upon successful completion of the interprovincial Red Seal examination.
column513: A college diploma or vocational training in travel or tourism is usually required.
column514: Certification with the Canadian Institute of Travel Counsellors (CITC) may be required. This certification is granted after completion of a 60 credit requirement obtained through any combination of work experience
column516: and successful completion of the advanced exam.
column517: Knowledge of a particular terrain or body of water
column518: demonstrated ability in the guided activity and relevant licences are required for employment in this group.
column519: Hot air balloon pilots require completion of 10 hours of ground school
column520: 16 hours of pilot-in-command experience and a Balloon Pilot Licence issued by Transport Canada.
column521: Certification in first aid and CPR (cardiopulmonary resuscitation) may be required.
column522: Completion of a provincial three- or four-year lineman/woman apprenticeship program \r\n or A combination of over four years of work experience in the trade and some high school
column523: college or industry courses in electrical technology is usually required for electrical power line and cable workers.
column524: Trade certification for powerline technicians is available
column525: Trade certification for powerline technicians (construction) is available
column527: Trade certification for distribution construction linemen/women is available
column529: Red Seal endorsement is also available to qualified powerline technicians upon successful completion of the interprovincial Red Seal examination.
column530: Completion of a college or other specialized program for silviculture workers or forestry crew workers may be required.
column531: Formal training in power saw operation and maintenance and several months of on-the-job training are usually provided.
column532: Experience as a logging and forestry labourer may be required.
column533: A chemicals application licence is required.
column534: Workplace hazardous materials information system (WHMIS) and transportation of dangerous goods (TDG) certificates may be required.
column535: A silvicultural worker\'s licence may be required.
